    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>creamed coconut </strong>and <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>to the<strong> </strong>pot<strong> </strong>with 400ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[500ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Cook for 6-8 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>coconut</strong> <strong>chicken breast khao soi</strong></p>",
